     <h1>President's Council</h1> 
     <h5>Roles and Responsibilities </h5> 
     <p>The President’s Council is an advisory group of faculty, staff and student representatives.&nbsp; The president typically convenes the group at least monthly during the academic year.&nbsp; </p> 
     <p></p> 
     <p>President’s Council responsibilities include serving as a sounding board for the president on significant college-wide issues; assisting the president to tend the vision of Westmont; advising the president on the development of the annual operating budget; considering the implications for the college of trends observed both internally and externally; and serving as a communication link with faculty, staff and students. </p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
